\f0\b\fs24 \cf0 Resource Management\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\qj

\f1\b0\fs20 \cf0 Equalizer uses a system-wide configuration server to optimally allocate and balance the available resources on the visualization system. The server is configured using a hierarchically structured configuration file to describe the available resources, and the combination of the resources for rendering. Equalizer applications can also run without a server, in which case they will automatically configure themselves for the local workstation. The central resource management enables system-wide resource reservation, allocation and scheduling, as well as the integration with other cluster scheduling software.}
